Appendicitis outbreak - Thailand (Cambodian refugees) 980325232927
[1
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 1998 18:07:46 +0000
From: Richard Doherty <Richard.Doherty@med.monash.edu.au>

Apart from _Y.enterocolitica_, other organisms classically associated with
pseudo-appendicitis include _Y. pseudotuberculosis_ and _Campylobacter_
spp. Campylobacter would normally cause occasional cases of
pseudoappendicitis [mixed in amongst many more conventional cases of
diarrhoea.
