[3
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 1998 12:31:25 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>

According to reference [below, 20% of older children and young
adults with _Y. enterocolitica_ can mimic appendicitis, a fact that has
caused epidemiologists to suspect _Y.e._ when there are increases in
appendectomies in a locality.
Easiest and most universal is Benenson A.S., APHA "Control of Communicable
Diseases
Manual" Sixteenth Ed., 1995.
